Summary (HGV): Account detailing receipts from the sale of oil and expenditure consisting of sums paid to individuals and household expenses.
Recto/Verso (HGV): On verso, three short lists of numbers
Publications (HGV): P. Tebt. 3 887 (Hunt, Arthur S. / Smyly, J. Gilbart / Edgar, Campbell Cowan; 1938)
Support/Dimensions (HGV): 5 papyri ; Frag. 1: 15 x 29.2 cm.; Frag. 1a: 10.5 x 13.5 cm.; Frag. 2: 15 x 27 cm.; Frag. 2a: 11.5 x 5.5 cm.; Frag. 2b: 6.5 x 9 cm. Frame (1) contains Frs. 1 and 1a; Frame (2), Frs. 2, 2a and 2b.
Subjects (HGV): Royal monopolies; Oils and fats; Merchants; Accounts, Ptolemaic period
Commentary (HGV): Zur Datierung vgl. BL VII, S. 273.
Lines (HGV): 8+ cols. (130+ lines) on recto along the fibers.
Note (local/note) (HGV): Bancroft Library, Univ. of Calif., Berkeley
Subjects (Tris): Liste; Abrechnung; Bank; Zahlungen; Namen; Berufe; Öl
